correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely ungrounded in the article and contains schema issues. Key problems: (1) Non-traceable or fabricated ALD details: ALD method set to TALD (not stated), IGZO precursors (“In–Ga bimetallic precursor,” DEZ) and co‑reactant (H2O), carrier/purging gas (N2), delivery method, deposition temperature (400 °C; this is an anneal temperature, not deposition), pressure, dosing/purge times, flow rates, nucleation period, saturation, uniformity, conformality—all absent from the paper. (2) Supercycle misrepresentation: IGZO ALD supercycle is not represented as In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO subcycles; instead a single “InGaZnO” subcycle is used, which is inconsistent with the IGZO ALD concept and not supported by the text. (3) Thickness control inconsistency: GPC 0.1 Å × 100 cycles yields ~1 nm, conflicting with the reported 10 nm IGZO film thickness; internal consistency is violated. (4) Schema violation: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null; if present it must be an object per schema—omit it or provide a valid object. (5) Material properties fabricated: refractive index, absorption, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, roughness, density, elemental concentration (10%), and atomic ratio (1.0:2.8:5.4) are not reported in the article; XPS discussion does not provide composition ratios. (6) Device properties: μ_FE = 25.3 cm^2/V·s, V_TH = 0.14 V, SS = 63.3 mV/dec are correct (Fig. 1d). However, on/off ratio (1e7) and device structure (“bottom-gate top-contact”) are not provided. (7) Missing processes: The article reports multiple passivation ALD processes (SiO2 process A/B and Al2O3 using TMA/H2O); the extraction provides only one process and omits these distinct ALD processes. Corrections needed: remove or mark unspecified any parameters not in the article; do not conflate anneal temperatures with deposition temperatures; model the IGZO supercycle per sub-oxide cycles if available; include separate processes for the passivation ALD steps (e.g., Al2O3 with TMA/H2O); fix plasmaPower typing; ensure GPC/cycle counts are consistent with 10 nm thickness; remove unsubstantiated material/optical/electrical values and on/off ratio, or replace with sourced values.

completeness.rationale: Extraction is largely non-traceable and incomplete relative to the article and schema intent. Key issues: (1) Multiple ALD processes described in the paper are not represented—at least the ALD Al2O3 passivation for stack 3 using TMA/H2O is missing as a separate process; only one IGZO process is provided. (2) Many process parameters are invented or misassigned: deposition temperature set to 400 °C (this is FGA/post-anneal temperature, not deposition); pressure, dosing/purge times, flow rates, carrier/purge gases, saturation and nucleation period are not reported in the article. (3) Supercycle design is incorrect for IGZO ALD—should list subcycles for In2O3, Ga2O3, ZnO; the extraction uses a single “InGaZnO” subcycle with no counts. (4) Reactant selection is unsubstantiated: “In-Ga bimetallic precursor,” DEZ and H2O for IGZO are not specified anywhere in the paper. (5) Thickness control is inconsistent: GPC 0.1 Å × 100 cycles yields 1 nm, conflicting with the 10 nm film thickness reported. (6) Material properties (refractive index, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, uniformity, conformality, composition ratios, roughness, density) and on/off ratio are not provided in the article and lack traceability. (7) Schema issue: plasmaPower is set to null though the field, if present, must be an object; also many filled values violate factual alignment requirements. The only values clearly grounded are device metrics for one condition (μ_FE 25.3 cm^2/V·s, V_TH 0.14 V, SS 63.3 mV/dec). To improve, add distinct processes for IGZO ALD and ALD Al2O3 passivation (with stated TMA/H2O), correct/remove unreported parameters, provide a proper IGZO supercycle definition, fix GPC–thickness consistency, and restrict properties to those traceable to the article.
